# Avatar Standard: Use UserAvatar Component

All user avatars in CentaurOS **must** use the standardized `UserAvatar` component to ensure consistent role-based color coding across the application.

## Required Import

```tsx
import { UserAvatar, UserAvatarStack } from "@/components/ui/user-avatar"
```

## DO NOT use raw Avatar components for users

```tsx
// ❌ WRONG - Do not do this
import { Avatar, AvatarFallback } from "@/components/ui/avatar"
<Avatar>
  <AvatarFallback className="bg-slate-100">JD</AvatarFallback>
</Avatar>

// ✅ CORRECT - Use UserAvatar instead
import { UserAvatar } from "@/components/ui/user-avatar"
<UserAvatar name="John Doe" role="Executive" size="md" />
```

## Role-Based Color System

The `UserAvatar` component automatically applies colors based on user role:

| Role | Background | Text | Use Case |
|------|------------|------|----------|
| `Founder` | `bg-orange-100` | `text-orange-700` | Company founders |
| `Executive` | `bg-blue-100` | `text-blue-700` | Executive team members |
| `Apprentice` | `bg-green-100` | `text-green-700` | Apprentices/interns |
| `AI_Agent` | `bg-purple-100` | `text-purple-600` | AI assistants |
| Default | `bg-slate-100` | `text-slate-600` | Any other role |

## Component Props

```tsx
interface UserAvatarProps {
  name: string | null | undefined    // User's full name for initials
  role?: string | null               // Role for color coding
  avatarUrl?: string | null          // Optional profile image
  size?: "xs" | "sm" | "md" | "lg" | "xl"  // Size variant
  showBorder?: boolean               // Add border styling
  className?: string                 // Additional classes
}
```

## Size Reference

| Size | Dimensions | Text Size | Use Case |
|------|------------|-----------|----------|
| `xs` | `h-4 w-4` | `text-[6px]` | Inline mentions, tiny indicators |
| `sm` | `h-6 w-6` | `text-[10px]` | Compact lists, dropdowns |
| `md` | `h-8 w-8` | `text-xs` | Default, cards, messages |
| `lg` | `h-10 w-10` | `text-sm` | Profile headers, prominent display |
| `xl` | `h-14 w-14` | `text-xl` | Large profile cards |

## Examples

### Single Avatar
```tsx
<UserAvatar name="Jane Smith" role="Founder" size="lg" />
<UserAvatar name="AI Assistant" role="AI_Agent" size="md" />
<UserAvatar name="John Doe" role="Executive" avatarUrl="/images/john.jpg" />
```

### Multiple Avatars (Stacked)
```tsx
<UserAvatarStack 
  users={assignees.map(a => ({
    id: a.id,
    name: a.full_name,
    role: a.role,
    avatarUrl: a.avatar_url,
  }))}
  size="md"
  max={4}
/>
```

### In a List/Dropdown
```tsx
{members.map(member => (
  <div className="flex items-center gap-2">
    <UserAvatar name={member.full_name} role={member.role} size="sm" />
    <span>{member.full_name}</span>
  </div>
))}
```

## When to Use Raw Avatar

The base `Avatar` component from `@/components/ui/avatar` should **only** be used for:
- Non-user avatars (e.g., organization logos, placeholder icons)
- Custom avatar implementations that don't represent a person

For any avatar representing a **user/person**, always use `UserAvatar`.
